The paper proposes a model for visual reasoning, which involves computer vision (CV) and artificial intelligence (AI). The model uses a program generator and an execution engine, which are both related to machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL), falling under the sub-categories of CS.CV, CS.AI, and CS.LG. The paper also evaluates the efficiency of the focus map, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL), falling under the sub-categories of CS.CL and CS.RO.
